ONGC Videsh Offers to Sell Russian Sokol Crude for June Loading

-- B y   A n n   K o h
-- 
2011-04-08T01:00:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/ongc-videsh-offers-to-sell-russian-sokol-crude-for-june-loading.html
ONGC Videsh Ltd., the overseas unit
of  India ’s biggest explorer, is offering 700,000 barrels of
 Russia ’s Sokol crude oil for loading between June 28 and June
30, according to a document e-mailed today to potential buyers.  The company, a wholly owned unit of Oil & Natural Gas
Corp., is entitled to a share of Sokol output from the Sakhalin-
1 project because it is one of the investors. The other partners
are Exxon Neftegas Ltd.,  Japan ’s Sakhalin Oil & Gas Development
Ltd. and two affiliates of Russia’s OAO Rosneft.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ann Koh in Singapore at 
 akoh15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Clyde Russell at 
 crussell7@bloomberg.net  